In a message dated 9/3/2002 12:46:31 PM Pacific Daylight Time, 
hazetguy(-at-)earthlink.net writes:
> i was considering taking a grinder wheel to the old weld down the center and 
> making a groove in the weld and just MIG welding it to keep them together.

Hi Jon,
That will work!  Just make sure to not over heat the torsion leaves and 
soften them.  In other words treat them like sheet metal and do small welds 
at a time, though never quench to cool them or risk hardening the leaves and 
have them snap off later.
Eric&Barb

